# Security

## Input Handling

- Sanitize all user-supplied input before rendering or processing
- Never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` — use React's safe rendering
- Validate file content before restore/import (check `data/restore.ts`)

## Collaboration & Encryption

- All shared room data MUST use end-to-end encryption (see `excalidraw-app/data/`)
- Never log or expose encryption keys or room IDs
- Do not store sensitive data in localStorage without encryption

## Dependencies

- No new packages that handle untrusted input without security review
- Audit any package that parses SVG, HTML, or binary formats

## Code Patterns

- No `eval()`, `new Function()`, or dynamic code execution
- No hardcoded secrets, tokens, or API keys in source files
- Use `URL` constructor for URL parsing — never string concatenation

## How to verify

- `grep -r "dangerouslySetInnerHTML" packages/ excalidraw-app/` — should return nothing
- `grep -r "eval(\|new Function(" packages/ excalidraw-app/` — should return nothing
- `grep -rE "(api_key|apiKey|secret|token)\s*=\s*[\"'][^\"']{8,}" packages/ excalidraw-app/` — no hardcoded secrets
- `yarn test:code` — ESLint security rules catch common patterns
